# .repo-boundary-denylist
#
# Strings that must NEVER appear in the public portbay-app repository.
# scripts/check-repo-boundaries.sh fails (locally and in CI) on any match.
#
# Each entry marks proprietary PortBay Cloud/Pro implementation, a secret, or a
# private endpoint that belongs ONLY in the private portbay-cloud repository.
# See docs/architecture/repo-boundaries.md for the full boundary policy.
#
# Format — three kinds of rule:
#   * `<string>`     forbidden CONTENT, matched as a fixed case-sensitive string.
#   * `re:<regex>`   forbidden CONTENT, matched as an extended regular expression.
#   * `path:<glob>`  forbidden PATH — this file may never be staged/committed,
#                    even with `git add -f` (it bypasses .gitignore, this does not).
#   Blank lines and lines beginning with `#` are ignored. In `path:` globs, `*`
#   matches across `/` (shell `case` semantics), so `secrets/*` and `*.pem` are
#   enough — no `**` needed.
#
# False positives (forbidden terms quoted in the boundary docs themselves,
# teaching examples, the committed `.env.example`) are excluded by path glob in
# `.repo-boundary-allow`. Add a glob there rather than weakening a rule here.

# --- Secret values / credentials (these never belong in version control) ---
STRIPE_SECRET
CUSTOMER_BILLING_SECRET
PAYMENT_WEBHOOK_SECRET
LICENSE_PRIVATE_KEY
ENTERPRISE_POLICY_SECRET
re:sk_live_[0-9A-Za-z]{16,}
re:sk_test_[0-9A-Za-z]{16,}
re:rk_live_[0-9A-Za-z]{16,}
re:-----BEGIN (RSA |EC |DSA |OPENSSH |PGP )?PRIVATE KEY-----

# --- Private Cloud/Pro implementation markers ---
PORT_CLOUD_PRIVATE
CLOUD_INTERNAL
PRO_INTERNAL
PRIVATE_TUNNEL_SERVER

# --- Private endpoints (the public app calls documented PUBLIC APIs only) ---
internal.portbay
private.portbay
port-cloud.internal

# --- Private package namespaces (the public repo must not depend on these) ---
@portbay-cloud/

# --- Paths that must NEVER be committed (blocks even `git add -f`) ---
# Real environment files and secrets (the committed template `.env.example` is
# allowlisted in .repo-boundary-allow).
path:.env
path:.env.*
# Private keys / certificates / keystores.
path:*.pem
path:*.key
path:*.p12
path:*.pfx
path:*.keystore
path:*.jks
# Secret bundles and local-only secret stores.
path:secrets/*
path:.secrets-local/*
path:*.secret
path:.dev.vars
# Signed/unsigned distributables belong on Releases, not in git.
path:*.dmg
path:*.app.zip
